{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Iron Guard was trying to take over the government.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Iron Guard were the Fascist Party.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In those days, the Iron Guard consisted of Cuza, Vaida, Octavius Goga, Zelea Codreanu.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They were the big Nazis there in Romania.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Then they had the Liberal Party.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "His name was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then they had the Socialist Party.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The leader of the Socialist Party was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were like the-- the most democrat-- more democratic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And once the fascists took over-- I think it was in 1937-- and we would go to shul every Monday.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And every Monday and Thursday, we would fast and recite [HEBREW] because we were in big trouble because they had in mind to liquidate the Jews, to burn down the shuls.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they were the fascists there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But a miracle happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The king had them all arrested and had them all executed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So in my village, I really don't remember any overt anti-Semitism because there were mostly Romanian people there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I-- and I really-- we got along very good-- very good with-- I mean, they were friends of mine, the-- when I went to school, they were my friends.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The people living in Comlausa, they were-- they-- they would work for my father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "My father had-- they were-- you know, we-- we socialized.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We-- we-- they were plain peasants.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we had sometimes problems, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Sometimes, it was men from the city.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "When I told you, in the mid-'30s, 1937, when those fascists, they came into the city.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they had like a pogrom, where they would go to Jewish shuls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And-- and they would beat up-- they would beat up people on the street.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they came to-- to the villages there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember, it was like a holiday like, Sukkos.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
